# SmartPRO AI conventions

Treat work as production, multi-tenant, end-to-end workflows. Full guidance lives under `docs/ai/` — start with `AI_OPERATING_SYSTEM.md` and `SMARTPRO_DOMAIN_GUARDRAILS.md`.

**Default task prefix:** Treat this as a production end-to-end workflow task; do not jump tasks, do not add unnecessary features, do not patch symptoms only, and do not call it complete without verification evidence.

**Non-negotiables:** Understand the flow before coding; server authority over client visibility; tenant isolation and RBAC on sensitive paths; minimal but complete changes; evidence before “done.”

Use `FEATURE_GATE_SKILL.md` before new scope, `END_TO_END_IMPLEMENTATION_SKILL.md` for substantive work, `QA_VERIFICATION_SKILL.md` before completion, and `BUG_TRIAGE_SKILL.md` for defects.
